04:20.792 --> 04:24.242
Are you going to commit yourself to me and only me?

04:25.346 --> 04:27.869
Are we doing this more than just to have fun?

04:27.949 --> 04:29.430
Is there a purpose here?

04:29.450 --> 04:31.092
Is there an end goal in mind?

04:31.552 --> 04:37.779
Do we share that same end purpose and end goal that we're committing to something?

04:37.799 --> 04:42.303
This is a DTR talk, define the relationship.

04:42.323 --> 04:52.754
Well, Israel is at this point in their history when God initiates this kind of conversation, this define the relationship conversation.

04:54.850 --> 04:59.877
And he does this with the people as they gather at the mountain.

04:59.897 --> 05:03.782
But this is not a new relationship that's being established.

05:03.802 --> 05:07.567
This is something that has already been in existence.

05:07.587 --> 05:12.193
Well, God, back in Genesis, came to a specific person named Abraham.

05:12.874 --> 05:18.802
And he came to Abraham and he said, I'm going to be your God and I'm going to be the God of your descendants too.

05:19.170 --> 05:30.087
So Abraham, from him, comes a multitude of people, comes this big, numerous nation, and they are captured or they are enslaved by the Egyptians.

05:31.049 --> 05:33.152
And then God does the work of deliverance.

05:33.192 --> 05:34.815
He frees them from slavery in Egypt.

05:34.835 --> 05:41.725
He's with them at the outset of their journey as they come out of Egypt and start making their way to the Promised Land.

05:42.747 --> 05:47.154
And now God brings them to this place where he has this conversation

05:47.266 --> 05:51.072
where he says, you know what, we need to define this relationship.

05:51.172 --> 05:52.934
I need to know, are you in?

05:53.095 --> 05:54.336
Are you fully committed?

05:54.356 --> 05:58.603
This relationship is for you, but I just need to know, are you in it?

05:59.063 --> 06:02.849
So what is it that Israel is agreeing to here?

06:04.411 --> 06:11.922
Well, in that the ancient Near East world in this context, formal relationships were established called covenants.

06:12.386 --> 06:19.635
covenants and one type of covenant that existed was called a suzerine vassal covenant or a relationship.

06:19.695 --> 06:21.818
It was a forming of a formal relationship.

06:22.539 --> 06:28.186
And in this specific relationship, the suzerine was the more powerful of the two parties.

06:28.887 --> 06:32.111
This was either the king or the stronger nation.

06:32.411 --> 06:34.674
And they would enter into a relationship

06:34.786 --> 06:46.200
They would initiate relationship with the vassal, the weaker of the two nations or the weaker of the two parties, usually somebody that was subject to the king or subject to this nation.

06:46.781 --> 06:48.783
And they would formalize this relationship.

06:48.823 --> 06:53.268
And like any relationship, there are some pieces to a relationship.

06:53.649 --> 06:57.874
There is commitment and there is purpose.

06:59.266 --> 07:10.402
Now this mosaic covenant that is established, that started off with Abraham and his relationship with God, and now it's continued and it's advanced through the Israelites.

07:10.803 --> 07:14.388
Well, this is a suzerine vassal covenant.

07:15.650 --> 07:27.026
And God, as the stronger part, he has the suzerine, he initiates this conversation, he initiates this defining of the relationship with Israel.

07:27.714 --> 07:35.062
And the first thing that he's impressing upon them as we look at this covenant relationship is commitment.

07:36.243 --> 07:39.766
God says, I want you to obey my voice.

07:40.327 --> 07:43.510
I want you to keep my covenant fully.

07:44.691 --> 07:51.478
The first commandment that God gives to them out of the Ten Commandments or the Ten Words, the Decalogue is, what is it?

07:52.259 --> 07:55.122
You shall have no other gods before me.

07:56.194 --> 08:01.379
Well, God is saying that you are to be exclusively for me.

08:01.399 --> 08:05.022
I don't want you to have eyes for anybody else.

08:05.122 --> 08:07.785
No longing looks.

08:07.805 --> 08:11.168
No stealing quick glances from other people.

08:11.248 --> 08:14.792
And definitely, no relations outside of this.

08:15.873 --> 08:20.997
The people are to look to the Lord, look to their king for everything they need.

08:21.658 --> 08:25.842
It's that big scary word when we're in a relationship, exclusive.

08:26.370 --> 08:30.176
there to be exclusively committed to the Lord.

08:30.216 --> 08:33.001
This is what the Lord is asking of them.

08:34.363 --> 08:40.373
But there's also an intention piece, a purpose piece.

08:40.453 --> 08:43.358
What is the reason behind this relationship?

08:43.378 --> 08:43.979
What is it for?

08:45.822 --> 08:52.914
Now for Abraham, now continued through to Israel, the relationship

08:53.090 --> 08:56.956
the reasoning for it has always been outward facing.

08:58.078 --> 09:05.109
God comes to Abraham in Genesis chapter 12 and he says, Abraham, I am going to make you into a great nation.

09:06.270 --> 09:11.338
I am going to bless you and all peoples on earth will be blessed through you.

09:11.538 --> 09:19.090
So yes, Israel is entering into this relationship or continuing this relationship with the Lord.

09:19.330 --> 09:26.719
And it is for their benefit and it is for their well-being, but ultimately it is for the people around them.

09:27.640 --> 09:32.205
It is for the nations to see and to know who this God is.

09:32.245 --> 09:46.642
And so the Lord in this intention or in this purpose, he says these words, you are to be, for me, a kingdom of priests and a holy nation.

09:47.714 --> 09:50.818
a kingdom of priests and a holy nation you are to be.

09:50.878 --> 09:56.166
And so just as priests, they represent God to the people.

09:56.706 --> 10:01.313
Well, so now Israel is to represent God to the surrounding nations.

10:01.793 --> 10:08.002
