Then we have been welcomed into God's family, adopted as His sons and daughters, because of what Jesus has done.

22:17.250 --> 22:19.052
We lay no claim to it.

22:19.373 --> 22:23.538
Arthur is saying, God, you love me because you tell me you love me and nothing I do.

22:23.618 --> 22:25.941
Nothing anyone else does can take that away.

22:25.981 --> 22:41.221
The third piece of Israel's identity that we're talking about here when he says the descendants of Jacob, the people of Israel, it's hinting at a future intention.

22:42.223 --> 22:44.786
There's a hint of future intention here.

22:46.082 --> 22:55.091
Now, when you talk about Jacob, when you talk about Israel, these names, it really says the house of Jacob, the house of Jacob, the people of Israel.

22:55.331 --> 23:04.681
Now, this takes us back to earlier on in Genesis, Genesis chapter 32, when Jacob, he meets with the Lord face to face.

23:04.741 --> 23:09.025
If you remember this story, Jacob, he wrestles with God.

23:10.046 --> 23:14.130
And as at this place, he names it Penil, which means the face of God.

23:14.658 --> 23:16.321
He encounters God.

23:16.401 --> 23:17.683
He comes before God.

23:18.344 --> 23:19.265
And God, what does he do?

23:19.305 --> 23:20.307
He changes him.

23:20.487 --> 23:22.150
God transforms him.

23:22.731 --> 23:23.812
And God gives him a new name.

23:24.133 --> 23:26.016
He says, Jacob, you're not going to be Jacob anymore.

23:26.056 --> 23:27.398
You're going to be Israel.

23:28.019 --> 23:29.181
Your name is going to be Israel.

23:29.241 --> 23:34.289
So now these slaves, these slaves are brought out of, out of Egypt.

23:34.309 --> 23:36.312
And they come before God's mountain.

23:36.733 --> 23:39.357
They come before to meet with God.

23:39.938 --> 23:42.642
And God's intention is to change them.

23:43.490 --> 23:47.500
God wants to make these people into His holy people.

23:47.981 --> 23:53.173
Again, so that they can go out and so that they can display to the nations who He is.

23:53.213 --> 23:58.546
So they come to Him and God's intention is to transform their lives.

23:59.266 --> 24:01.530
And they'll do this by the living out of the law.

24:01.831 --> 24:04.816
They'll love the Lord, their God with all their hearts, soul, mind, and strength.

24:04.856 --> 24:06.679
They'll love their neighbors as themselves.

24:07.020 --> 24:14.994
They'll build the tabernacle with all of its furnishings so that the people might know that this is a God who dwells in our midst.

24:16.514 --> 24:18.737
These are, this is the identity of Israel.

24:19.217 --> 24:21.200
They are the people of the king.

24:21.220 --> 24:22.421
They belong to him.

24:22.822 --> 24:24.083
They've done nothing to earn it.

24:24.103 --> 24:25.405
Nobody can take it away.

24:25.865 --> 24:30.651
And God's intention is to not leave them where they're at, but to change them into his holy people.

24:30.691 --> 24:36.018
So when God comes to them and has this defining conversation, Israel, are you going to obey me?

24:36.038 --> 24:37.119
Are you going to follow me?

24:37.179 --> 24:42.706
Well, of course, they have no, they think nothing else in the say, yes, Lord.

24:43.307 --> 24:45.970
Yes, Lord, of course we're gonna follow you.

24:46.370 --> 24:49.055
You, who else loves us as much as you do?

24:49.095 --> 24:54.967
Who else is able to set us free from the powers of sin and darkness and Pharaoh?

24:55.367 --> 24:59.756
Who else exercises creation to stand up for us in our behalf?

25:00.077 --> 25:05.267
Who else has claimed us as their own, as his own against all the powers of the world?

25:05.708 --> 25:07.451
Yes, Lord, we will do what you say.

25:07.511 --> 25:09.074
We will live as your people.

25:09.602 --> 25:11.164
We will follow your covenant.

25:11.545 --> 25:18.075
We will be in this committed relationship with you and only you as your people so that the nations may see.

25:18.115 --> 25:23.884
Identity comes before mission.

25:25.166 --> 25:26.288
Who we are.

25:26.889 --> 25:28.812
We are people of the king.

25:29.793 --> 25:31.115
We are God's people.

25:31.135 --> 25:33.058
He has claimed us as his own.

25:34.681 --> 25:36.023
We are people who have not earned it.

25:36.183 --> 25:37.906
We have done nothing to deserve it.

25:38.338 --> 25:40.761
He welcomes us into this covenant of grace.

25:42.102 --> 25:46.086
And we are people who have been brought before the face of God.

25:47.788 --> 25:51.512
Oh, God Himself has come to us in the person of Jesus Christ.

25:52.833 --> 25:55.496
In a sense, we have seen Him face to face.

25:57.298 --> 25:59.060
He has revealed Himself to us.

26:00.922 --> 26:04.786
And not only does He live among us,

26:07.330 --> 26:09.272
No, He lives inside of us.

26:10.774 --> 26:15.138
We don't get holy by following the law and its regulations.

26:15.699 --> 26:19.323
No, we get holy by the regeneration of the Holy Spirit.

26:19.904 --> 26:28.613
Because of what Jesus Christ has done in dying and rising and ascending to the Father and sending the Holy Spirit to us, we are made holy.

26:29.134 --> 26:33.298
We are transformed from sinners into saints.

26:35.234 --> 26:40.960
Our mission statement, learning to live and love like Jesus as broken people saved by grace.

26:41.701 --> 26:49.149
We go out into the world, conformed into the image of Christ, but deeply knowing that this is who we are.

26:49.630 --> 26:58.800
We have been claimed by the king, we have been claimed by the master of the universe as his very own, as his treasured possession, as his special possession.

27:01.043 --> 27:04.146
So yes, the call is to be fully committed.

27:04.962 --> 27:16.922
The call is to go out into the nations, to go out into the community, shining the love and light of Christ, revealing the character of our holy God, but this is God's mission.

27:17.182 --> 27:18.404
This is God's mission.

27:19.927 --> 27:21.489
We do this through His strength.

27:22.110 --> 27:26.037
We do this through His power, and we do this for His glory.

27:26.818 --> 27:29.202
All of God's people said, amen.

27:36.162 --> 27:42.512
All right, just a couple of areas where you might feel a sense of responsiveness.

27:43.614 --> 27:46.899
Again, our offering, what shall I return to the Lord for His goodness to me?

27:48.161 --> 27:54.070
We always want to be people, not just who hear the word and receive it, but who go out and put it into practice.

27:54.530 --> 28:01.581
So I want you to think about, think about a neighbor in acquaintance that you might be able to bless with one of these prepackaged meals.

28:01.802 --> 28:04.626
Get them in your mind this week and be praying about it.

28:04.834 --> 28:17.691
And then come next week or have it pre-arranged where you can pick up one of these pre-arranged meals that you can go to this person to help with food insecurity or help with loneliness to start building relationships.

28:17.711 --> 28:18.652
So have that in your mind.

28:19.513 --> 28:20.314
Who is that neighbor?

28:20.334 --> 28:23.779
Identify that person or pray that the Lord would lay somebody on your heart.

28:25.000 --> 28:29.266
Maybe it's responding to this question, have I been operating out of my own strength?

28:29.826 --> 28:38.361
Have I been trying to earn God's favor through, earn God's holiness through what I do rather than who he's made me to be as his son or daughter?

28:38.401 --> 28:43.530
Have I been trying to find my identity outside of the Lord?

28:43.971 --> 28:47.517
Do I need to offer the prayer, Lord, help me to know myself as your child?

28:47.838 --> 28:49.481
How is God calling you to respond?

28:50.042 --> 28:54.770
Take a minute or two and allow the spirit of the Lord to speak to you.

